530
00:37:34.391 --> 00:37:35.684
Heaven!

531
00:37:41.856 --> 00:37:43.608
I can't believe I found Samaritan.

532
00:37:43.692 --> 00:37:44.943
Wrong.

533
00:37:45.026 --> 00:37:47.612
You're just a dude who gets hit by a car.

534
00:37:47.696 --> 00:37:48.822
gets his bones broken.

535
00:37:48.905 --> 00:37:50.281
and eats mad ice cream.

536
00:37:50.365 --> 00:37:53.785
I eat this stuff to cool my body down.

537
00:37:53.868 --> 00:37:55.537
Why don't you just drink some ice water?

538
00:37:55.620 --> 00:37:57.372
I don't like the taste.

539
00:37:59.457 --> 00:38:01.668
- Can I have some? No. undefined
- undefined

540
00:38:01.751 --> 00:38:04.421
Sorry.
I need it for emergencies.

541
00:38:05.922 --> 00:38:08.091
Why were you steaming?

542
00:38:08.174 --> 00:38:11.720
You know anything about binary fission.
cellular thermodynamics?

543
00:38:11.803 --> 00:38:14.139
What?
I'm 13 years old.

544
00:38:14.222 --> 00:38:16.474
You know what happens during a heat stroke?

545
00:38:16.558 --> 00:38:18.852
When I get hurt. my body overheats.

546
00:38:18.935 --> 00:38:20.937
and if I don't cool it down.

547
00:38:22.647 --> 00:38:23.815
my heart explodes.

548
00:38:23.898 --> 00:38:26.151
That is not human.

549
00:38:26.234 --> 00:38:29.404
Wait.
Is this how it was for Nemesis?

550
00:38:30.697 --> 00:38:32.407
You guys were brothers. right?

551
00:38:33.324 --> 00:38:35.910
Enough with the Nemesis stuff.

552
00:38:35.994 --> 00:38:37.474
Why don't you go have some ice cream?

553
00:38:37.954 --> 00:38:39.039
Thanks.

554
00:38:46.212 --> 00:38:48.048
You saved my dad once.

555
00:38:48.131 --> 00:38:50.216
Where do you come up with this stuff?

556
00:38:50.300 --> 00:38:52.343
Have you ever looked up
the word "delusional."

557
00:38:52.427 --> 00:38:54.637
because that's what you are.
You're delusional.

558
00:38:54.721 --> 00:38:56.431
I'm not delusional.
I'm serious.

559
00:38:56.514 --> 00:38:58.016
You saved my dad.

560
00:38:58.099 --> 00:38:59.184
He used to boost cars.

561
00:39:00.226 --> 00:39:02.020
You caught him one night.

562
00:39:02.103 --> 00:39:04.689
And instead of busting him.
you talked to him.

563
00:39:04.773 --> 00:39:06.649
What'd he do.
write fairytales for a living?

564
00:39:06.733 --> 00:39:08.318
No. he died.

565
00:39:14.282 --> 00:39:16.576
Let's see if we can wake these people up.

566
00:39:38.306 --> 00:39:39.307
My bad.

567
00:39:57.909 --> 00:39:59.327
There they go.

568
00:40:00.161 --> 00:40:02.539
We can do better than that.

569
00:40:02.622 --> 00:40:04.475
I swear. I'm gonna
beat the crap out of you.

570
00:40:04.499 --> 00:40:06.626
- Oh. yeah?
- Yeah! Bring it!

571
00:40:08.962 --> 00:40:09.963
Hey!

572
00:40:22.559 --> 00:40:25.228
Granite City...

573
00:40:25.311 --> 00:40:28.731
Who comes to help the helpless?

574
00:40:29.899 --> 00:40:32.735
Who is our hero?

575
00:40:32.819 --> 00:40:34.112
Is that Nemesis?

576
00:40:34.195 --> 00:40:37.448
I am back to start a revolution

577
00:40:37.532 --> 00:40:41.536
for all the people this city left behind.

578
00:40:43.872 --> 00:40:46.082
Our movement

579
00:40:46.166 --> 00:40:50.879
will put the power back in
the hands of the people.

580
00:40:53.006 --> 00:40:57.802
It's time to take back what is yours!

581
00:41:03.433 --> 00:41:05.143
Put this on.
Here you go. my man.

582
00:41:06.728 --> 00:41:11.316
The revolution starts now!

583
00:41:17.071 --> 00:41:20.909
Nemesis! Nemesis! Nemesis!

584
00:41:20.992 --> 00:41:25.413
Nemesis! Nemesis! Nemesis!

585
00:41:35.465 --> 00:41:36.507
Go!

586
00:41:37.425 --> 00:41:38.426
Go!

587
00:42:23.554 --> 00:42:24.865
City officials are in shock

588
00:42:24.889 --> 00:42:26.599
from last night's events.

589
00:42:26.683 --> 00:42:29.978
A mysterious blackout
and gang of men in Nemesis masks

590
00:42:30.061 --> 00:42:32.230
triggered a long night
of looting last night.

591
00:42:32.313 --> 00:42:33.940
Several people were injured.

592
00:42:34.023 --> 00:42:35.775
With the town on edge already

593
00:42:35.858 --> 00:42:38.152
with high unemployment
and poverty on the rise.

594
00:42:38.236 --> 00:42:41.990
some say it's only a matter of time
before the city implodes.

595
00:43:04.095 --> 00:43:05.096
Hey.

596
00:43:07.432 --> 00:43:08.933
What do I have to do?

597
00:43:09.017 --> 00:43:11.394
Throw you under a bus
to make you stop following me?

598
00:43:12.312 --> 00:43:13.688
Samaritan wouldn't do that.

599
00:43:13.771 --> 00:43:16.024
What if he was having a bad day?

600
00:43:17.483 --> 00:43:18.484
Come on.

601
00:43:23.740 --> 00:43:24.949
So. what's in the bag?

602
00:43:25.033 --> 00:43:26.701
Hey. hey. It's a camera.
Don't touch.

603
00:43:26.784 --> 00:43:28.870
- Where you taking it to?
- To a pawn shop.

604
00:43:28.953 --> 00:43:30.330
Sounds horrible.

605
00:43:33.291 --> 00:43:35.251
What do you even do all day?

606
00:43:35.335 --> 00:43:36.627
Fix things and get depressed?

607
00:43:41.049 --> 00:43:42.800
I'm a troglodyte.

608
00:43:42.884 --> 00:43:44.886
- Do you know what that is?
- No clue.

609
00:43:44.969 --> 00:43:48.514
It's Greek for a man who dwells in a cave.
See. I'm a caveman.

610
00:43:48.598 --> 00:43:51.017
I live in a tiny apartment.
and it's fine.

611
00:43:51.100 --> 00:43:53.686
I'm good with it.
I like being alone.

612
00:43:53.770 --> 00:43:56.439
You know what bothers me?
What really depresses me?

613
00:43:59.025 --> 00:44:00.276
Being around other people.

614
00:44:00.360 --> 00:44:01.778
Follow me?

615
00:44:01.861 --> 00:44:03.237
No.

616
00:44:03.321 --> 00:44:04.882
- Sure. you do. No. undefined
- undefined

617
00:44:04.906 --> 00:44:06.574
That doesn't make any sense.

618
00:44:06.657 --> 00:44:08.618
You save people.
That's not a loner.

619
00:44:08.701 --> 00:44:10.620
Smells like bullshit to me.

620
00:44:13.539 --> 00:44:16.417
You got big balls.
I'll give you that.

621
00:44:16.501 --> 00:44:18.520
So. how much do you think
you're gonna get off the camera?

622
00:44:18.544 --> 00:44:19.545
I don't know.

623
00:44:20.338 --> 00:44:21.506
10 bucks. 20 bucks?

624
00:44:21.589 --> 00:44:24.175
God. what are you.
an accountant or something?

625
00:44:24.258 --> 00:44:27.178
Do me a favor.
stay here while I go in there.

626
00:44:27.261 --> 00:44:28.262
Still want me to come in?

627
00:44:28.346 --> 00:44:30.723
No. yeah. That's why I said.
"Wait here."

628
00:44:30.807 --> 00:44:31.808
Hey!

629
00:44:33.726 --> 00:44:34.894
What are you looking at?

630
00:44:44.445 --> 00:44:45.738
Sorry.

631
00:44:48.950 --> 00:44:51.744
What?
You just let that happen?

632
00:44:51.828 --> 00:44:53.913
Should've thrown him
over a tree or something.

633
00:44:56.999 --> 00:44:58.709
I'm disappointed.

634
00:45:02.922 --> 00:45:03.923
Stay out.

635
00:45:06.968 --> 00:45:09.011
What the hell did you do?

636
00:45:09.095 --> 00:45:11.681
Just snapped off.
It's falling apart. like both of us.

637
00:45:11.764 --> 00:45:13.558
Yeah. well. speak for yourself.

638
00:45:16.269 --> 00:45:17.979
This is solid brass.

639
00:45:18.062 --> 00:45:20.481
I know.
But even brass gets tired.

640
00:45:20.565 --> 00:45:21.875
I'm taking this
out of your account.

641
00:45:21.899 --> 00:45:22.900
That's fair enough.

642
00:45:22.984 --> 00:45:26.279
Another Sunday.
another piece of junk.

643
00:45:26.362 --> 00:45:28.698
- Give you $25.
- Whoa. Really?

644
00:45:28.781 --> 00:45:29.824
Here we go again.

645
00:45:29.907 --> 00:45:30.908
It's not a Canon.

646
00:45:30.992 --> 00:45:33.995
How about $50
and I take your picture with it?

647
00:45:34.078 --> 00:45:36.164
Okay.

648
00:45:39.834 --> 00:45:41.687
Hey. come on! What are you doing?

649
00:45:41.711 --> 00:45:43.230
- Stop! Thief!
- Look at this. See?

650
00:45:43.254 --> 00:45:45.465
This is what happens when you let

651
00:45:45.548 --> 00:45:48.384
a couple of genetic freaks
try to fix your city.

652
00:45:48.468 --> 00:45:50.678
People gotta get rid of their own problems.

653
00:45:50.761 --> 00:45:54.307
or their problems
gonna get rid of them. right?

654
00:45:54.390 --> 00:45:55.641
Right.

655
00:45:55.725 --> 00:45:57.435
How many bad guys did you fight at once?

656
00:45:57.518 --> 00:45:58.853
100.

657
00:45:59.437 --> 00:46:00.438
Wow.

658
00:46:00.521 --> 00:46:02.732
How strong are you?

659
00:46:02.815 --> 00:46:04.859
I'm still pretty strong.
You saw that.

660
00:46:04.942 --> 00:46:07.403
But not like I once was.

661
00:46:07.487 --> 00:46:10.781
Things start to fall apart when
you stop caring. and I stopped caring

662
00:46:12.158 --> 00:46:13.826
a long time ago.

663
00:46:13.910 --> 00:46:15.328
How far can you jump?

664
00:46:15.411 --> 00:46:17.747
Then. maybe over 10 cars.

665
00:46:17.830 --> 00:46:19.415
Now. nine.

666
00:46:19.499 --> 00:46:21.459
No way.
Let's see you do it.

667
00:46:21.542 --> 00:46:24.504
No. forget it. I'm not gonna
wreck my knees entertaining you.

668
00:46:25.963 --> 00:46:27.882
Have you ever had to jump off a building?

669
00:46:27.965 --> 00:46:30.259
No. but I've thrown
a lot of people off 'em.

670
00:46:30.343 --> 00:46:31.761
I'm just kidding.

671
00:46:31.844 --> 00:46:33.721
Man. I've told you too much.

672
00:46:35.640 --> 00:46:37.350
You can trust me.

673
00:46:37.433 --> 00:46:38.684
You should know that.

674
00:46:53.658 --> 00:46:54.951
You ever get scared?

675
00:46:57.203 --> 00:46:58.746
Why? Are you scared of something?

676
00:47:03.417 --> 00:47:06.462
- Just...
- Sure. I get scared.

677
00:47:06.546 --> 00:47:09.090
Come on.
Everybody does.

678
00:47:09.173 --> 00:47:11.300
Fear. that's natural.

679
00:47:11.384 --> 00:47:13.594
But you'd still fight.

680
00:47:13.678 --> 00:47:15.263
Yeah. when necessary.

681
00:47:15.346 --> 00:47:17.807
But I don't want to.
I don't like it.

682
00:47:19.392 --> 00:47:22.895
When I get scared. the first
thing I think about is running.

683
00:47:22.979 --> 00:47:25.106
And I always freeze up.

684
00:47:25.189 --> 00:47:27.608
Hey. Come here.

685
00:47:28.943 --> 00:47:31.237
That's the smart thing to do.

686
00:47:31.320 --> 00:47:33.990
Street fighting is for fools.

687
00:47:34.073 --> 00:47:36.659
Why would you wanna get into a
fight with some stranger

688
00:47:36.742 --> 00:47:38.411
who has nothing to do with your life.

689
00:47:39.412 --> 00:47:40.955
who could take your life?

690
00:47:43.916 --> 00:47:47.503
What you're doing is right. okay?

691
00:47:50.631 --> 00:47:53.342
You better get going
before your mother calls the cops.

692
00:47:53.426 --> 00:47:55.720
All right.
Good night. Joe.

693
00:47:56.637 --> 00:47:57.638
Sam.

694
00:47:59.223 --> 00:48:00.308
Let me see your watch.

695
00:48:15.865 --> 00:48:17.700
I'll try.

696
00:48:17.783 --> 00:48:18.826
But no promises.

697
00:48:20.328 --> 00:48:21.537
Thanks. Joe.

698
00:48:21.621 --> 00:48:22.997
You're welcome.

699
00:48:32.089 --> 00:48:33.567
For the second consecutive week.

700
00:48:33.591 --> 00:48:35.926
rioters filled the streets of Granite City.

701
00:48:36.010 --> 00:48:38.095
Another spontaneous blackout followed.

702
00:48:38.179 --> 00:48:39.639
which some attribute to a man

703
00:48:39.722 --> 00:48:43.517
claiming to be
the presumed dead villain. Nemesis.

704
00:48:43.601 --> 00:48:45.227
Under the cover of darkness.

705
00:48:45.311 --> 00:48:48.022
organized looters
vandalized financial institutions

706
00:48:48.105 --> 00:48:49.774
wearing Nemesis masks.

707
00:48:50.483 --> 00:48:52.109
Is Nemesis back?

708
00:48:52.193 --> 00:48:54.570
That is what the city
is asking this morning.

709
00:49:02.286 --> 00:49:03.579
Morning!

710
00:49:04.705 --> 00:49:06.374
What's so good about it?

711
00:49:06.457 --> 00:49:08.584
What's the matter?
You sleep okay?

712
00:49:08.668 --> 00:49:10.294
I got a migraine.

713
00:49:10.378 --> 00:49:12.538
You'll get 'em when you get older.
They're a nightmare.

714
00:49:12.588 --> 00:49:16.008
Well. funny you say that.

715
00:49:16.092 --> 00:49:18.844
I always have nightmares about
you getting hit by that car.

716
00:49:18.928 --> 00:49:22.348
- And since I saved you and all...
- Yeah. thank God for that.

717
00:49:22.431 --> 00:49:24.058
...I was wondering.

718
00:49:25.017 --> 00:49:27.812
if you could teach me how to fight?

719
00:49:27.895 --> 00:49:30.022
- No.Please. undefined
- undefined

720
00:49:30.106 --> 00:49:31.667
- Forget it. Come on. undefined
- undefined

721
00:49:31.691 --> 00:49:33.984
I wanna learn.
I wanna be like you.

722
00:49:34.068 --> 00:49:35.361
Please?

723
00:49:36.362 --> 00:49:37.655
Be like me.

724
00:49:39.907 --> 00:49:41.450
All right.

725
00:49:41.534 --> 00:49:43.828
Meet me on the roof after work. okay?

726
00:49:43.911 --> 00:49:45.788
Okay.
Thanks.

727
00:49:45.871 --> 00:49:47.957
What a bad idea.

728
00:49:58.926 --> 00:50:01.303
Hey. Sorry I'm late.

729
00:50:01.387 --> 00:50:03.305
That's all right.

730
00:50:03.389 --> 00:50:05.069
- Come on. All right. undefined
- undefined

731
00:50:05.141 --> 00:50:07.035
Let's see you move around little bit.
See what you got.

732
00:50:07.059 --> 00:50:08.978
- All right. Come on. undefined
- undefined

733
00:50:09.061 --> 00:50:10.396
I don't have a lot of patience.

734
00:50:10.479 --> 00:50:12.064
Chill out. old man.

735
00:50:12.148 --> 00:50:14.108
- Oh-ho.
- Okay. All right.

736
00:50:19.363 --> 00:50:21.115
Look at speedy boy.

737
00:50:21.198 --> 00:50:22.199
Wow.

738
00:50:22.283 --> 00:50:23.868
Where'd you learn to rip like that?

739
00:50:23.951 --> 00:50:25.870
My father taught me when I was four.

740
00:50:25.953 --> 00:50:27.329
I quit when he died.

741
00:50:28.956 --> 00:50:30.458
- That's impressive.
- Thanks.

742
00:50:32.126 --> 00:50:33.127
Hey.

743
00:50:34.628 --> 00:50:35.629
Hit my hand.

744
00:50:39.383 --> 00:50:40.426
No. no.
Hit my hand.

745
00:50:40.509 --> 00:50:41.802
It's kind of hard to miss.

746
00:50:41.886 --> 00:50:44.305
- Why do I do that?
- What?

747
00:50:44.388 --> 00:50:46.766
- Back up?
- Yeah. Like a coward.

748
00:50:46.849 --> 00:50:48.684
- Why?
- 'Cause you're lucky.

749
00:50:48.768 --> 00:50:50.519
I don't fight back.
How am I lucky?

750
00:50:50.603 --> 00:50:52.813
You're lucky because you were raised right.

751
00:50:52.897 --> 00:50:54.440
What if you don't got a choice?

752
00:50:54.523 --> 00:50:57.777
Like. let's say if someone
messes with your mom.

753
00:50:57.860 --> 00:51:00.196
Well. then you sucker punch the
fool and run like hell.

754
00:51:01.655 --> 00:51:03.115
Is that fair. though?

755
00:51:03.199 --> 00:51:05.659
Hey. if life was fair.
everyone would get along.

756
00:51:05.743 --> 00:51:06.911
But guess what?
They don't.

757
00:51:07.411 --> 00:51:08.871
Crazy.

758
00:51:08.954 --> 00:51:10.748
- What? You. undefined
- undefined

759
00:51:10.831 --> 00:51:11.832
Well...

760
00:51:14.335 --> 00:51:15.753
Really?

761
00:51:15.836 --> 00:51:17.797
That's what you get for sucker punching me.

762
00:51:17.880 --> 00:51:19.131
Come on.
We'll get some ice.

763
00:51:19.215 --> 00:51:21.050
- Oh. my God!
- What were you thinking?

764
00:51:21.133 --> 00:51:22.134
I don't know.

765
00:51:23.177 --> 00:51:25.304
You know I'm built like a tank.

766
00:51:25.387 --> 00:51:26.931
I think it's broken.

767
00:51:27.014 --> 00:51:29.308
Nah. it's not broken.

768
00:51:29.391 --> 00:51:30.768
Just bruised.

769
00:51:31.602 --> 00:51:33.187
This will fix it up.

770
00:51:34.230 --> 00:51:35.648
Here you go.

771
00:51:35.731 --> 00:51:37.107
Put your paw in here.

772
00:51:38.150 --> 00:51:39.735
Thanks.

773
00:51:39.819 --> 00:51:41.904
Why you like working
on all this old junk so much?

774
00:51:42.571 --> 00:51:43.614
It's therapeutic.

775
00:51:43.697 --> 00:51:46.283
You see this old toaster?

776
00:51:50.871 --> 00:51:53.123
See?
Breaking things comes easy.

777
00:51:53.207 --> 00:51:56.752
Now. fixing them.
that helps me relax and focus.

778
00:51:56.836 --> 00:52:00.130
and I figure. some of these old
things deserve a second chance.

779
00:52:00.214 --> 00:52:02.132
Like you?

780
00:52:02.216 --> 00:52:03.592
Nah. I'm just kidding.

781
00:52:05.678 --> 00:52:08.389
Whatever happened between you and Nemesis?

782
00:52:08.472 --> 00:52:10.266
You just don't quit. do you?

783
00:52:15.271 --> 00:52:16.814
Good thing Nemesis is gone.

784
00:52:20.568 --> 00:52:24.154
Maybe. but none of you know
what really happened.

785
00:52:24.238 --> 00:52:27.032
All I know is that Nemesis died that night.

786
00:52:27.116 --> 00:52:28.117
Do it.

787
00:52:30.202 --> 00:52:33.622
Albert Casler says that Nemesis
had a plan to blow up the power station.

788
00:52:33.706 --> 00:52:35.040
And throw the city

789
00:52:35.666 --> 00:52:36.876
into anarchy and chaos.

790
00:52:38.377 --> 00:52:40.880
He doesn't know what the hell
he's talking about.

791
00:52:43.173 --> 00:52:44.550
Go home.

792
00:52:46.969 --> 00:52:48.345
Go on!

793
00:53:03.736 --> 00:53:05.529
Little man.

794
00:53:05.613 --> 00:53:07.156
What's going on. kid?

795
00:53:07.239 --> 00:53:08.240
Nothing much.

796
00:53:08.324 --> 00:53:09.742
Come to earn that $100?

797
00:53:12.536 --> 00:53:14.830
Yeah.
Decided I wanna punch up.

798
00:53:16.457 --> 00:53:17.499
Get in.

799
00:53:17.583 --> 00:53:18.876
Sil.

800
00:53:22.171 --> 00:53:23.422
Let's go.

801
00:53:45.027 --> 00:53:46.028
Hey. kid.

802
00:53:56.205 --> 00:53:57.665
So. you got a family?

803
00:53:58.540 --> 00:53:59.917
Just my mom.

804
00:54:00.000 --> 00:54:01.669
It's more than I had.

805
00:54:01.752 --> 00:54:02.753
I never had shit.

806
00:54:04.296 --> 00:54:06.507
Not till Cyrus found me.

807
00:54:06.590 --> 00:54:10.094
Sleeping in a car out back when
I was. like. eight years old.

808
00:54:12.346 --> 00:54:14.223
He woke me up.
So. I bit him.

809
00:54:17.851 --> 00:54:19.103
You been with him ever since?

810
00:54:21.230 --> 00:54:22.356
He's my family.

811
00:54:24.024 --> 00:54:25.275
Same for all them.

812
00:54:27.111 --> 00:54:28.529
Cyrus gave us this.

813
00:54:33.492 --> 00:54:35.911
So. don't disappoint my family.
Sam.

814
00:54:38.205 --> 00:54:40.249
I'll take everything from you.

815
00:54:48.507 --> 00:54:49.508
Ready?

816
00:54:49.591 --> 00:54:50.926
Yep.

817
00:54:51.010 --> 00:54:52.737
This is gonna be complicated.
so pay attention.

818
00:54:52.761 --> 00:54:54.471
Right.

819
00:54:54.555 --> 00:54:57.975
If a cop comes. you whistle.

820
00:55:01.562 --> 00:55:02.563
That's it?

821
00:55:02.646 --> 00:55:04.023
Let me hear.

822
00:55:05.858 --> 00:55:07.651
No.

823
00:55:13.282 --> 00:55:14.408
What?

824
00:55:18.162 --> 00:55:20.473
Vicinity of
34th and 3rd. all units in the area.

825
00:55:20.497 --> 00:55:21.737
Do it like that. kid.

826
00:55:23.417 --> 00:55:24.418
Sorry.

827
00:55:24.501 --> 00:55:25.586
Hello. Officer.

828
00:55:26.378 --> 00:55:27.379
Here you go.

829
00:55:36.263 --> 00:55:37.681
You gotta learn how to whistle.

830
00:56:36.573 --> 00:56:39.201
Notice how a cop don't look like much

831
00:56:39.284 --> 00:56:40.619
without a badge and a gun.

832
00:56:47.709 --> 00:56:49.336
Why are you screwing with me?

833
00:56:51.088 --> 00:56:52.506
I paid you to look the other
way.

834
00:56:53.132 --> 00:56:55.050
That power station.

835
00:56:55.134 --> 00:56:57.054
it controls the grid to this
part of the country.

836
00:56:58.470 --> 00:57:00.722
Yeah. So what?

837
00:57:00.806 --> 00:57:03.433
You almost blew the whole plan.

838
00:57:03.517 --> 00:57:05.894
I wasn't gonna sit by and watch
you assholes plant bombs.

839
00:57:06.520 --> 00:57:08.188
Okay. Super Cop.

840
00:57:08.814 --> 00:57:09.815
Sil.

841
00:57:16.613 --> 00:57:18.323
Okay. okay!
I'll leave!

842
00:57:18.407 --> 00:57:20.367
I'll leave. please!
Stop it!

843
00:57:20.450 --> 00:57:22.050
I can't hear you.
It's very loud.

844
00:57:22.077 --> 00:57:23.078
I'll get out.

845
00:57:23.162 --> 00:57:25.306
You'll never hear from me again. I swear.
I won't tell a soul.

846
00:57:25.330 --> 00:57:26.582
What?

847
00:57:26.665 --> 00:57:28.458
I'll leave!
Just turn it off. please!

848
00:57:31.378 --> 00:57:32.379
Stop.

849
00:57:36.383 --> 00:57:37.384
Thank you.

850
00:57:46.143 --> 00:57:48.770
Leave and never come back.

851
00:57:49.980 --> 00:57:51.565
You'll never hear from me again.

852
00:57:51.648 --> 00:57:52.941
I promise.

853
00:58:01.992 --> 00:58:03.744
Thank you.
Thank you.

854
00:58:03.827 --> 00:58:05.329
Welcome.

855
00:58:12.044 --> 00:58:14.254
Always give people hope.

856
00:58:34.566 --> 00:58:35.692
Help!

857
00:58:39.696 --> 00:58:41.281
Yo. stop!

858
00:58:41.365 --> 00:58:43.075
Come here. fat boy.
I'll smack you.

859
00:58:43.158 --> 00:58:44.243
This turd owe me money.

860
00:58:44.743 --> 00:58:46.245
What?

861
00:58:46.328 --> 00:58:49.581
You gotta choose.
either him or it's us.

862
00:58:49.665 --> 00:58:51.059
You either with us or you ain't.
Come on.

863
00:58:51.083 --> 00:58:52.334
Sam! Help!

864
00:58:52.417 --> 00:58:54.169
Get a good grip.
Hold him up.

865
00:59:00.342 --> 00:59:02.261
Jace! Get the hell out of here!

866
00:59:02.344 --> 00:59:03.762
Go!
Go!

867
00:59:07.933 --> 00:59:09.535
- Hold him up!
- Come here.

868
00:59:09.559 --> 00:59:10.602
Hold him up.

869
00:59:11.186 --> 00:59:12.187
Hold his arm out!

870
00:59:12.271 --> 00:59:14.189
Let me go!

871
00:59:14.898 --> 00:59:15.899
No!

872
00:59:15.983 --> 00:59:17.609
Hey!
Hey!

873
00:59:18.151 --> 00:59:19.152
Cry for me.

874
00:59:20.696 --> 00:59:21.697
Do it.

875
00:59:52.019 --> 00:59:54.229
Burn it up! Yeah!

876
01:00:22.966 --> 01:00:24.509
Would you look at this shit?

877
01:00:25.844 --> 01:00:27.596
Come on. come on. come on.

878
01:00:31.850 --> 01:00:33.685
Doctor Davis. telephone. please.

879
01:00:33.769 --> 01:00:36.188
Doctor Davis. telephone. please.

880
01:00:39.775 --> 01:00:41.526
Hey. Sam.
How you doing. buddy?

881
01:00:43.653 --> 01:00:45.048
What the hell happened with my son?

882
01:00:45.072 --> 01:00:46.531
Some kids beat him up.

883
01:00:48.158 --> 01:00:49.409
And you couldn't stop them?

884
01:00:51.286 --> 01:00:52.287
No.

885
01:00:53.288 --> 01:00:55.707
Some hero you are.

886
01:00:55.791 --> 01:00:57.667
Doctor Blair. Doctor Blair.

887
01:00:59.920 --> 01:01:01.160
When the bombs go off

888
01:01:01.213 --> 01:01:02.357
that we planted at the power station.

889
01:01:02.381 --> 01:01:05.300
the central grid goes. okay?
That means

890
01:01:05.384 --> 01:01:07.969
- all of the power that comes in and out...
- Hey! Hey!

891
01:01:08.053 --> 01:01:09.179
He's alive.

892
01:01:09.262 --> 01:01:11.473
- Who?
- The old guy!

893
01:01:11.556 --> 01:01:13.433
Not a chance.
Do you see that damn car?

894
01:01:13.517 --> 01:01:16.357
Cuz. I'm telling you. I saw the guy
walking around like nothing hit him.

895
01:01:16.436 --> 01:01:18.647
- Man. we hit him solid.
- Who?

896
01:01:18.730 --> 01:01:20.440
Some old man that was messing with Reza.

897
01:01:20.524 --> 01:01:22.150
And you popped him?

898
01:01:22.234 --> 01:01:23.610
Hundred percent.

899
01:01:27.781 --> 01:01:29.408
Think I'd like to meet this old man.

900
01:02:18.373 --> 01:02:20.250
Sweet. Thanks.

901
01:02:40.061 --> 01:02:41.897
My boss wants to meet you. old man.

902
01:02:43.815 --> 01:02:45.484
You're coming with us.

903
01:02:45.567 --> 01:02:49.613
Well. my advice is
you should think long and hard

904
01:02:49.696 --> 01:02:53.825
before you make a big. big mistake.

905
01:02:54.326 --> 01:02:55.327
Tiny.

906
01:02:57.996 --> 01:03:00.165
Well. why don't you just show me?

907
01:03:00.248 --> 01:03:01.249
No problem.

908
01:03:05.295 --> 01:03:06.546
Get him. Get him!

909
01:03:13.053 --> 01:03:14.262
Oh. shit!

910
01:03:45.710 --> 01:03:46.711
Really?

911
01:03:49.089 --> 01:03:50.090
Fly.

912
01:04:07.566 --> 01:04:09.025
Hey!
Hey!

913
01:04:10.777 --> 01:04:12.445
Did you just do that?

914
01:04:12.529 --> 01:04:14.239
You threw that bad man through the wall.

915
01:04:14.322 --> 01:04:15.824
How'd you do that?

916
01:04:15.907 --> 01:04:17.492
Well. little girl.

917
01:04:18.577 --> 01:04:20.120
you didn't see anything.

918
01:04:20.203 --> 01:04:24.291
See. that hole was already there.
That's an optical illusion.

919
01:04:24.374 --> 01:04:27.252
- No. what I saw was you threw that man--
- No. no.

920
01:04:27.335 --> 01:04:29.055
- You actually didn't see...
- Hey. old man.

921
01:04:30.171 --> 01:04:31.172
Try this.

922
01:04:33.466 --> 01:04:34.593
Mayday!

923
01:04:35.760 --> 01:04:37.012
Come on!

924
01:04:51.151 --> 01:04:53.153
Sorry. kid.
You all right?

925
01:04:54.154 --> 01:04:55.363
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

926
01:05:01.620 --> 01:05:02.787
All right.
I gotta go. kid.

927
01:05:03.413 --> 01:05:04.414
Nice meeting you.

928
01:05:06.207 --> 01:05:07.208
What?

929
01:05:12.255 --> 01:05:14.674
Is there hope on the horizon?

930
01:05:14.758 --> 01:05:18.386
As Granite City grapples with
continued violence and mob uprisings

931
01:05:18.470 --> 01:05:20.513
caused by the return of Nemesis.

932
01:05:20.597 --> 01:05:23.391
could this remarkable footage. just in.

933
01:05:23.475 --> 01:05:25.644
mean that Samaritan is back. too?

934
01:05:25.727 --> 01:05:26.853
Mayday!

935
01:05:33.193 --> 01:05:35.028
Now. this young girl saw everything.

936
01:05:35.111 --> 01:05:36.380
Tell me. do you think it was Samaritan?

937
01:05:36.404 --> 01:05:37.798
My grandma told me a story

938
01:05:37.822 --> 01:05:40.450
about how Samaritan
saved her from a speeding bus.

939
01:05:40.533 --> 01:05:42.202
That man saved my life.

940
01:05:42.285 --> 01:05:43.787
And all he was missing was a mask.

941
01:05:43.870 --> 01:05:45.306
Just incredible.

942
01:05:45.330 --> 01:05:47.248
How did that make you feel?

943
01:05:49.250 --> 01:05:50.543
- Hey.
- Hey.

944
01:05:50.627 --> 01:05:52.045
I think you were on the news.

945
01:05:52.128 --> 01:05:53.129
Yeah. I saw that.

946
01:05:53.213 --> 01:05:54.881
Yeah.

947
01:05:54.964 --> 01:05:56.675
You should see the other guy.

948
01:05:56.758 --> 01:05:58.551
- What's with the bag?
- It's nothing.

949
01:05:58.635 --> 01:06:00.261
So what happened to the other guy?

950
01:06:00.345 --> 01:06:01.388
Sucker punched him.

951
01:06:02.597 --> 01:06:03.890
But then. I forgot to run.

952
01:06:03.973 --> 01:06:05.767
Hey. I never wanted you to get hurt.

953
01:06:05.850 --> 01:06:08.395
Well. I did.

954
01:06:08.478 --> 01:06:10.730
And now my mom won't believe a word I say.

955
01:06:10.814 --> 01:06:14.150
She won't listen to me when I tell her
something bad is going to happen.

956
01:06:14.234 --> 01:06:15.443
What's gonna happen?

957
01:06:15.527 --> 01:06:17.153
Cyrus. the guy from the junkyard.

958
01:06:18.947 --> 01:06:21.074
He's planning something
with the power stations.

959
01:06:21.157 --> 01:06:22.951
Call the cops because I want no part of it.

960
01:06:23.034 --> 01:06:24.911
But you're the only one that can help.

961
01:06:33.461 --> 01:06:35.547
You help people.

962
01:06:38.591 --> 01:06:40.552
I can't help anyone. Sam.

963
01:06:40.635 --> 01:06:42.512
So you run away?

964
01:06:42.595 --> 01:06:44.806
You're just as bad as everybody else.

965
01:06:51.146 --> 01:06:52.147
Sam.

966
01:06:57.110 --> 01:06:58.111
He's here!

967
01:06:58.194 --> 01:06:59.195
He's here!

968
01:07:00.321 --> 01:07:02.073
He's here!

969
01:07:02.157 --> 01:07:03.867
What are you talking about?

970
01:07:03.950 --> 01:07:05.535
- You didn't watch the news yet?
- No.

971
01:07:09.372 --> 01:07:11.541
...remarkable footage. just in...

972
01:07:11.624 --> 01:07:14.419
mean that Samaritan is back. too?

973
01:07:19.632 --> 01:07:23.511
Just incredible.
Tell me. how did that make you feel?

974
01:07:23.595 --> 01:07:27.599
Gosh. I guess.
I'm just happy that someone's looking out.

975
01:07:28.975 --> 01:07:31.060
Someone is. indeed. looking out.

976
01:07:31.144 --> 01:07:33.938
And the question is catching on
in Granite City.

977
01:07:34.022 --> 01:07:35.857
Samaritan lives?

978
01:07:35.940 --> 01:07:37.233
What if it is him?

979
01:07:37.317 --> 01:07:38.651
If he's Samaritan?

980
01:07:38.735 --> 01:07:40.695
C. it's him.
It's Samaritan.

981
01:07:40.779 --> 01:07:42.906
What happens if he comes looking for Nemesis?

982
01:07:42.989 --> 01:07:45.867
What happens if he tries to stop us?

983
01:07:45.950 --> 01:07:47.136
I'm not gonna let him.

984
01:07:47.160 --> 01:07:49.829
I'm gonna show him who the real hero is.

985
01:07:49.913 --> 01:07:52.457
After 25 years. he comes back.

986
01:08:07.889 --> 01:08:09.682
Where's the damn watch?
Where is it?

987
01:08:41.589 --> 01:08:42.966
Oh. shit.

988
01:08:45.176 --> 01:08:46.344
No.
No.

989
01:08:46.427 --> 01:08:48.179
Ma.

990
01:08:48.263 --> 01:08:49.722
Ma.
Ma!

991
01:08:49.806 --> 01:08:51.432
On the second floor.

992
01:08:51.516 --> 01:08:53.059
On the end.

993
01:09:06.865 --> 01:09:09.158
Hey. It's this floor.

994
01:09:35.518 --> 01:09:37.186
Ma! Ma!

995
01:09:37.270 --> 01:09:39.188
- I'm in here!
- Ma.

996
01:09:42.358 --> 01:09:43.359
- What?
- We gotta go.

997
01:09:43.443 --> 01:09:45.243
- We gotta go right now. Ma.
- What? Go where?

998
01:09:45.278 --> 01:09:46.279
Just listen to me. okay?

999
01:10:27.654 --> 01:10:28.821
Mom. Mom. come on.

1000
01:10:28.905 --> 01:10:30.281
Get the kid!

1001
01:10:36.079 --> 01:10:37.288
Ma.

1002
01:10:39.958 --> 01:10:41.167
Come on.
Come on.

1003
01:10:42.669 --> 01:10:44.045
We gotta go!

1004
01:10:44.128 --> 01:10:46.381
Miss White. it's Tiffany Cleary
from downstairs.

1005
01:10:46.464 --> 01:10:47.775
- Please open the door.
- No. no. You can't come in.

1006
01:10:47.799 --> 01:10:49.717
- Ma! Ma!
- Go away!

1007
01:10:55.390 --> 01:10:56.432
Come on.

1008
01:10:57.684 --> 01:10:59.284
Hey! You're dead!

1009
01:11:01.604 --> 01:11:03.022
They're going up!

1010
01:11:07.777 --> 01:11:08.987
- Shit!
- Aw.

1011
01:11:09.779 --> 01:11:11.489
What a nice family.

1012
01:11:11.572 --> 01:11:12.865
Get away from my son.

1013
01:11:12.949 --> 01:11:14.367
- Mom.
- Come here.

1014
01:11:18.413 --> 01:11:19.956
- No. no.
- No.

1015
01:11:20.039 --> 01:11:21.374
Sam. just stay close to me.

1016
01:11:21.457 --> 01:11:22.625
What do you want from my son?

1017
01:11:23.418 --> 01:11:24.627
Stay away from my kid.

1018
01:11:24.711 --> 01:11:26.791
Or you're gonna see a side of me
you don't wanna see.

1019
01:11:28.006 --> 01:11:29.132
What do you want?

1020
01:11:30.174 --> 01:11:32.343
- I just wanna talk to my pal.
- No.

1021
01:11:32.427 --> 01:11:35.346
You're not talking to him.
You don't talk to him without me.

1022
01:11:35.430 --> 01:11:36.973
- No. No! No.
- Mom. No.

1023
01:11:37.056 --> 01:11:38.599
No. No.
Don't touch her!

1024
01:11:38.683 --> 01:11:40.476
- Hey.
- No!

1025
01:11:40.560 --> 01:11:41.728
- Come on. Let's go.
- Mom!

1026
01:11:41.811 --> 01:11:44.272
- No. no. Sam!
- I promise. everything will be fine.

1027
01:11:44.355 --> 01:11:45.815
No!

1028
01:11:45.898 --> 01:11:47.442
- No!
- Really. Sil?

1029
01:11:47.525 --> 01:11:48.735
She's alive. ain't she?

1030
01:11:48.818 --> 01:11:49.986
You bitch!

1031
01:11:50.069 --> 01:11:52.447
- Who's the bitch?
- You!

1032
01:11:52.530 --> 01:11:53.740
Don't touch me!

1033
01:11:56.200 --> 01:11:57.618
- Hey.
- Get your hands off of me.

1034
01:12:00.830 --> 01:12:02.123
I knew I liked you.

1035
01:12:03.249 --> 01:12:04.667
He's coming for you.

1036
01:12:06.127 --> 01:12:07.670
He's gonna come for me!

1037
01:12:07.754 --> 01:12:10.798
Yeah.
That's why I gotta take you.

1038
01:12:10.882 --> 01:12:13.259
So Nemesis can finally kill Samaritan.

1039
01:12:14.469 --> 01:12:15.988
Granite City is on edge

1040
01:12:16.012 --> 01:12:18.139
and gearing up for
another night of violence.

1041
01:12:18.222 --> 01:12:20.850
Officials are frantically
searching for any information

1042
01:12:20.933 --> 01:12:22.769
related to the return of Nemesis.

1043
01:12:22.852 --> 01:12:24.103
They fear his reign of terror

1044
01:12:24.187 --> 01:12:25.188
has only just begun.

1045
01:12:25.271 --> 01:12:27.166
This is the final call
for all passengers...

1046
01:12:27.190 --> 01:12:28.667
- ...travelling to Albuquerque
- A widespread power outage

1047
01:12:28.691 --> 01:12:30.294
- on Windsor Bus 43.
- has prevented first responders

1048
01:12:30.318 --> 01:12:31.736
from accessing parts of the city

1049
01:12:31.819 --> 01:12:33.130
while alarming gangs of Nemesis followers...

1050
01:12:33.154 --> 01:12:34.715
Final call. Windsor 43.

1051
01:12:34.739 --> 01:12:38.242
...have sparked a wave of destruction
that shows no sign of stopping.

1052
01:12:38.326 --> 01:12:41.621
Now. more than ever.
Granite City needs a hero.

1053
01:12:45.875 --> 01:12:46.876
Sam.

1054
01:12:47.919 --> 01:12:49.670
Sam. I fixed your watch.

1055
01:12:49.754 --> 01:12:50.755
Sam.

1056
01:12:55.134 --> 01:12:57.470
- You okay?
- No. Sam.

1057
01:12:59.347 --> 01:13:00.389
What happened?

1058
01:13:00.473 --> 01:13:01.474
They took him.

1059
01:13:03.726 --> 01:13:05.311
Sam.
Sam.

1060
01:13:05.394 --> 01:13:06.395
Who took him?

1061
01:13:07.647 --> 01:13:09.690
Cyrus.
Cyrus.

1062
01:14:06.038 --> 01:14:08.374
Our foot soldiers
are fanned out across the city.

1063
01:14:09.167 --> 01:14:10.459
Once those lights go out...

1064
01:14:11.794 --> 01:14:14.088
- ...it's ready to blow.
- Good.

1065
01:14:14.172 --> 01:14:15.532
- That's down the block.
- Shut up.

1066
01:14:17.175 --> 01:14:18.885
What happened to punching up. huh?

1067
01:14:18.968 --> 01:14:20.154
You gotta burn before you build.

1068
01:14:20.178 --> 01:14:22.597
Well. you're gonna fail.
Just like Nemesis.

1069
01:15:19.737 --> 01:15:21.530
Come on. move it!

1070
01:15:55.982 --> 01:15:57.358
Oh. shit!

1071
01:16:05.366 --> 01:16:06.367
Kid!

1072
01:16:07.785 --> 01:16:08.869
Sam!

1073
01:16:12.665 --> 01:16:14.208
Sam!

1074
01:16:18.504 --> 01:16:20.006
Let go!

1075
01:16:22.174 --> 01:16:23.676
I came for the kid.

1076
01:16:23.759 --> 01:16:25.136
He's fine.

1077
01:16:25.219 --> 01:16:26.220
Are you all right?

1078
01:16:26.304 --> 01:16:28.264
Yeah.
Yeah.

1079
01:16:32.768 --> 01:16:34.353
Samaritan.

1080
01:16:35.104 --> 01:16:37.148
Welcome. good guy.

1081
01:16:37.231 --> 01:16:38.399
You came.

1082
01:16:40.109 --> 01:16:42.903
You really came.

1083
01:16:42.987 --> 01:16:47.616
I never saw Samaritan care so much
about anyone in my part of town before.

1084
01:16:51.287 --> 01:16:52.872
Let him go.

1085
01:16:59.503 --> 01:17:02.006
And we'll do this. you and me.

1086
01:17:05.843 --> 01:17:06.844
No.

1087
01:17:08.512 --> 01:17:10.556
I want him to watch his hero fall.

1088
01:17:12.558 --> 01:17:14.310
To see what everyone should know.

1089
01:17:15.311 --> 01:17:17.146
that you're a fake.

1090
01:17:22.651 --> 01:17:26.697
No one can help you
but yourself. good guy.

1091
01:17:29.909 --> 01:17:31.327
Joe!

1092
01:17:31.410 --> 01:17:32.453
Come on!

1093
01:17:32.536 --> 01:17:33.537
Stay back!

1094
01:17:35.831 --> 01:17:38.501
Come on. good guy.

1095
01:17:45.174 --> 01:17:47.051
- Go! Go!
- Joe! Fight back!

1096
01:17:51.347 --> 01:17:54.058
Joe!
Do something!

1097
01:17:59.355 --> 01:18:02.316
Watch your hero fall. Sam.

1098
01:18:02.400 --> 01:18:04.860
- See me finish what Nemesis started.
- Bring it!

1099
01:18:06.362 --> 01:18:09.365
Come on. Joe!
Fight back. please!

1100
01:18:22.795 --> 01:18:25.172
Now you know how Nemesis felt!

1101
01:18:25.923 --> 01:18:27.258
How we all felt!

1102
01:18:29.844 --> 01:18:32.888
No one comes to save you. good guy.

1103
01:18:37.810 --> 01:18:41.272
You keep calling me the "good guy."

1104
01:18:45.526 --> 01:18:47.736
I'm not the good guy.

1105
01:18:55.411 --> 01:18:57.455
I'm the bad guy!

1106
01:18:58.289 --> 01:18:59.290
Nemesis?

1107
01:18:59.373 --> 01:19:00.499
What?

1108
01:19:25.065 --> 01:19:27.234
Shoot!
Shoot!

1109
01:19:41.207 --> 01:19:42.416
Sil...

1110
01:19:44.376 --> 01:19:45.377
Come here!

1111
01:19:46.045 --> 01:19:47.087
Let go!

1112
01:20:09.276 --> 01:20:10.653
Let go of me!

1113
01:20:12.780 --> 01:20:14.573
Did you know who he was?

1114
01:20:16.992 --> 01:20:18.744
- Did you know?
- No!

1115
01:20:24.750 --> 01:20:25.876
Sil.

1116
01:20:25.960 --> 01:20:27.294
Sil.

1117
01:20:27.378 --> 01:20:28.629
Sil!

1118
01:21:01.745 --> 01:21:03.205
Let me go!

1119
01:21:04.707 --> 01:21:05.749
Tie him up!

1120
01:21:10.212 --> 01:21:11.213
Let me go!

1121
01:21:11.297 --> 01:21:12.715
Let me go!

1122
01:22:01.013 --> 01:22:02.014
Come on!

1123
01:22:13.901 --> 01:22:15.152
Going my way?

1124
01:22:24.495 --> 01:22:26.622
You're nothing like him!

1125
01:22:26.705 --> 01:22:27.956
We'll see.

1126
01:22:31.418 --> 01:22:32.878
Wipe the city dark.

1127
01:24:04.219 --> 01:24:05.387
Oh. man.

1128
01:24:12.811 --> 01:24:13.812
Enough.

1129
01:24:16.148 --> 01:24:17.149
Yeah.

1130
01:24:18.609 --> 01:24:21.236
Did you bring another toy?

1131
01:24:21.320 --> 01:24:22.738
Is that what you did?

1132
01:24:39.463 --> 01:24:41.131
Have a blast.

1133
01:25:15.624 --> 01:25:16.875
Anybody. help!

1134
01:25:34.852 --> 01:25:36.228
Help!

1135
01:25:36.311 --> 01:25:37.312
Sam!

1136
01:25:37.396 --> 01:25:38.772
I'm over here!

1137
01:25:51.451 --> 01:25:52.619
Come on!

1138
01:25:52.703 --> 01:25:53.787
We gotta get outta here.

1139
01:25:57.207 --> 01:25:58.292
Joe. behind you!

1140
01:26:07.843 --> 01:26:09.511
Give up. old man.

1141
01:26:37.080 --> 01:26:40.125
You should've stayed buried. old man.

1142
01:26:40.208 --> 01:26:44.129
Look at you.
You're weak. You're pathetic!

1143
01:26:44.212 --> 01:26:47.674
I'm doing what you never could. your plan.

1144
01:26:47.758 --> 01:26:49.301
The power station. the grid.

1145
01:26:50.260 --> 01:26:52.471
I'm gonna tear it all down.

1146
01:26:52.554 --> 01:26:55.682
There never was a plan!

1147
01:26:55.766 --> 01:26:57.809
- It was a trap!
- Liar!

1148
01:26:57.893 --> 01:26:59.102
Joe!

1149
01:26:59.186 --> 01:27:00.312
Look at him. Sam.

1150
01:27:01.688 --> 01:27:03.315
Look at your hero.

1151
01:27:05.359 --> 01:27:07.694
He betrayed you. Sam.

1152
01:27:07.778 --> 01:27:09.154
He betrayed everyone.

1153
01:27:10.364 --> 01:27:14.326
But no one betrays me!

1154
01:27:18.413 --> 01:27:19.748
Come on!

1155
01:27:23.126 --> 01:27:24.169
No!

1156
01:27:57.953 --> 01:27:59.705
No one's gonna save you now.

1157
01:28:32.738 --> 01:28:33.947
No.

1158
01:28:34.031 --> 01:28:35.032
No!

1159
01:28:42.205 --> 01:28:44.291
No. please!
Please! Please!

1160
01:28:45.959 --> 01:28:49.171
No! No! No!

1161
01:28:49.671 --> 01:28:51.256
No!

1162
01:28:52.299 --> 01:28:53.300
No!

1163
01:29:56.446 --> 01:29:57.739
Joe?

1164
01:30:01.993 --> 01:30:03.161
- What?
- Water!

1165
01:30:22.889 --> 01:30:23.890
Joe!

1166
01:30:24.850 --> 01:30:26.518
Joe. come on.
Fight. Joe!

1167
01:30:27.727 --> 01:30:28.895
Joe!

1168
01:30:28.979 --> 01:30:29.980
No.

1169
01:30:31.731 --> 01:30:32.732
No.

1170
01:30:34.151 --> 01:30:36.069
Don't give up. Joe. come on!

1171
01:30:38.113 --> 01:30:39.406
Joe!

1172
01:30:42.784 --> 01:30:44.452
Come on. fight. Joe.

1173
01:30:57.340 --> 01:30:58.383
Thanks. kid.

1174
01:30:59.342 --> 01:31:00.343
That's

1175
01:31:01.845 --> 01:31:02.888
some sucker punch.

1176
01:31:05.849 --> 01:31:07.434
Come on. Joe. let's get up.

1177
01:31:07.517 --> 01:31:08.518
Yeah.

1178
01:31:10.145 --> 01:31:11.146
I got you.

1179
01:31:15.025 --> 01:31:16.026
Come on.

1180
01:31:26.077 --> 01:31:28.163
All right.
Don't be afraid.

1181
01:31:28.788 --> 01:31:29.915
We got this.

1182
01:31:29.998 --> 01:31:31.249
Wait. what?

1183
01:31:36.129 --> 01:31:37.130
Oh. my...

1184
01:31:38.673 --> 01:31:41.885
No!

1185
01:31:53.438 --> 01:31:54.606
That hurt.

1186
01:31:58.068 --> 01:31:59.611
Holy shit.

1187
01:32:00.987 --> 01:32:02.239
Come on. dude.

1188
01:32:03.490 --> 01:32:05.075
Man. we gotta get outta here.

1189
01:32:05.158 --> 01:32:06.284
Come on.

1190
01:32:07.702 --> 01:32:09.579
You got it.
Let's go.

1191
01:32:10.789 --> 01:32:11.915
Is it true?

1192
01:32:11.998 --> 01:32:14.292
- There's people coming. let's go...
- Is it true?

1193
01:32:17.212 --> 01:32:18.380
What. that I'm him?

1194
01:32:18.964 --> 01:32:21.549
Yeah. it's true.

1195
01:32:23.718 --> 01:32:25.011
You can fix that.

1196
01:32:26.429 --> 01:32:28.473
I've seen you fix things before.

1197
01:32:29.015 --> 01:32:30.558
You can change.

1198
01:32:34.354 --> 01:32:36.523
Kid. let me tell you something.

1199
01:32:37.274 --> 01:32:41.111
If there was only bad people
doing bad things.

1200
01:32:41.194 --> 01:32:42.946
it'd be easy to get rid of 'em.

1201
01:32:43.822 --> 01:32:46.241
But the real truth is.

1202
01:32:46.324 --> 01:32:50.829
good and bad live in everybody's heart.

1203
01:32:52.205 --> 01:32:56.376
And it's gonna be up to you
to make the right choice.

1204
01:32:58.962 --> 01:33:00.839
And I know you will.

1205
01:33:03.925 --> 01:33:05.802
Up here.
Fourth floor.

1206
01:33:08.722 --> 01:33:10.015
All right. let's go.

1207
01:33:26.406 --> 01:33:27.717
Protestors here witnessed

1208
01:33:27.741 --> 01:33:30.660
this building behind me
going up in flames.

1209
01:33:30.744 --> 01:33:34.122
A figure. who some think
may have been Samaritan.

1210
01:33:34.205 --> 01:33:35.874
carried a young boy to safety.

1211
01:33:35.957 --> 01:33:38.060
We're hearing some cheers right now.
It's the boy. Let's go.

1212
01:33:38.084 --> 01:33:40.211
Shut up!
Nemesis!

1213
01:33:41.046 --> 01:33:42.380
Hey. kid.
What's your name?

1214
01:33:42.464 --> 01:33:44.382
It's Sam.
His name is Sam.

1215
01:33:44.924 --> 01:33:46.426
You were right. Sam.

1216
01:33:46.509 --> 01:33:49.637
Well. Sam. can you answer the question
that everyone has been asking?

1217
01:33:49.721 --> 01:33:51.431
Yes. Samaritan lives.

1218
01:33:51.514 --> 01:33:53.224
You're certain that it's really him?

1219
01:33:54.059 --> 01:33:57.103
Man. it was hot in there.
Fire all around.

1220
01:33:57.187 --> 01:34:00.523
Samaritan came right through
the flames and helped me.

1221
01:34:00.607 --> 01:34:03.360
That was Samaritan!
He saved my life.

1222
01:34:05.695 --> 01:34:09.407
Samaritan! Samaritan! Samaritan!
